{
  "stem": "7177.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was not aware at all that anything was wrong with me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Tima and Ali-- Tima-- the gentleman who had, you know, saved us, and brought us, and did all these dangerous things for us-- was a part of the underground.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he did unbelievable things, of which I will name a few of them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was-- among-- he had-- was hiding-- I do not know exactly, but I would say 15 Jewish people in a forest.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Hidden in the forest, in a-- they had dug a hole underneath trees.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think they were-- I do not know exactly, but I think they were about 15.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had-- yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Tima had then, of course, his friends in the underground who would go there twice or three times per week to bring food to these people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you can just really imagine how dangerous that was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They did not-- one of the people who he also rescued was an American [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] airman who had to been in hiding with my brother [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for about two weeks.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Tima went to where my brother was and took his bicycle and another bicycle that we bought some place.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Albert Stern is the name of the American navigator.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was a navigator, he was not a pilot.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he then was transported the same way that we were transported originally, originally.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Only that was much more dangerous.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, we were only Jews, and the Jews would have just been, you know, ended.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But he was an American pilot, navigator, who was being rescued by Dutch underground people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Also about 25 miles, the same-- you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
